high.title: Activity (com.sysmanager.Administrator) is vulnerable to Android Task Hijacking/StrandHogg.
high.description: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask". It is then possible for other applications to place a malicious activity on top of the activity stack resulting in Task Hijacking/StrandHogg 1.0 vulnerability. This makes the application an easy target for phishing attacks. The vulnerability can be remediated by setting the launch mode attribute to "singleInstance" or by setting an empty taskAffinity (taskAffinity="") attribute. You can also update the target SDK version (22) of the app to 28 or higher to fix this issue at platform level.
